The paper deals with problems related to planar graphs, their connectivity, and their geometric properties. Specifically, it focuses on edge insertion and deletion operations that aim to increase the connectivity of a given planar straight-line graph while minimizing the total edge length. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves algorithms and complexity analysis, which are typical of the data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and graph theory (cs.GT) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also discusses optimization problems and bounds, which are relevant to the computational complexity (cs.CC) sub-category.
